    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "Do I need an API key to use this skill?",
        "answer": "Yes. You need a RunComfy account and token. Run runcomfy login to authenticate interactively, or set the RUNCOMFY_TOKEN environment variable for automated environments."
      },
      {
        "question": "Which image model should I use for text in images?",
        "answer": "Use GPT Image 2. It is the best model for rendering exact text, headlines, and multilingual typography inside images."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I edit existing images with this skill?",
        "answer": "Yes. The skill supports image-to-image editing through models like Nano Banana 2 Edit and GPT Image 2 Edit."
      },
      {
        "question": "How many reference images can I use?",
        "answer": "This depends on the model. Nano Banana 2 supports up to 20 input images, FLUX 2 supports up to 4, and GPT Image 2 supports up to 10."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is this skill safe to use?",
        "answer": "Yes. The skill only invokes the runcomfy CLI with structured JSON inputs. It never runs arbitrary shell commands or accesses sensitive files."
      },
